reviewText: Hilarious! I got a signed copy as a gift for my wife. Rhys is a stand-up guy!
A great whimsical show with fabulous standup sandwiched in amongst an engaging, fantasy inspired narrative.  And there is Flight of the Conchord's Jemaine Clement making an audible cameo!

If you are from the same town, county, state or country it might be very funny otherwise not so much. The Sci-Fi marketing elements totally misleading and has ensure that I will not watch "Rhys Darby" in the future.
Was expecting sci/fi humor.  In actually he mostly does Kiwi dating and such jokes
So good...there were some times when I thought I would turn it off but as soon as it finished I was so happy, I couldn't stop laughing!

Rhys comedy is a total adventure.  If you have midwestern-only american ears  Go watch the cable guy.  This is comedy gold.  Kiwi Izzard wits with Ross Nobel abstract disorientation with other references to be determined later.  If you don't get those references, read the second sentence.  A welcome respite from the grey world of the USA in 2018.  When is the next DVD?
Laugh out load funny, and sneakily high concept. Great for any comedy fan. I also so Darby live recently, and probably missed half the show because I laughing too much. Must watch!
Great lessons in how not to die of skingone and proper pickpocketing techniques.
A comic apparently from New Zealand.  Not very funny to my American ears.  No doubt a scream in NZ.
